    &lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;p&gt;Putting ink on paper stimulates a part of the brain called the Reticular Activating System, or the RAS.  It works by giving more importance to the things you are actively focusing on.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424052748704631504575531932754922518&#34;&gt;study from 2010&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;fully-engages-your-brain&#34; &gt;Fully engages your brain
